“The extended negotiation stage has
ended today without reaching a deal,” Sintramienergetica union
says on website.
*Deal could still be reached this evening, union negotiator
Humberto Suarez says in phone interview from Santa Marta
*Co. didn’t immediately reply to an e-mail and phone call
outside normal business hours seeking comment
*NOTE: Talks on wages, safety conditions started May 29, were
scheduled to end June 17; negotiations extended to July 7 after
parties failed to reach agreement
*NOTE: Coal is Colombia’s biggest export after oil
*NOTE: Workers at Cerrejon, Colombia’s biggest coal mine, went
on strike for more than a month starting Feb. 7 after failing to
reach wage agreement with management; Finance Ministry estimates
strike cut 1Q GDP growth by 50bps  To contact the reporter on this story:
